==English==
===Noun===
'''epicycle'''
#{{astronomy}} (''in Ptolemaic cosmology'') a small [[circle]], moving around the [[circumference]] of a larger circle having the [[earth]] at its centre; the supposed [[orbit]] of a [[planet]]
#{{mathematics}} any circle whose circumference [[roll]]s around that of another circle, thus creating a [[hypocycloid]] or [[epicycloid]]

====Translations====
*Finnish: [[episykli]]

